reviews.review_text: The old home of The Old American.  Be super awesome if it was still that but at least you can get ultra rad DL chicken burgers and strips and reminisce about the place that used to be here 30 years ago. I dont know if I ever met Papa Gus
Just dropped in for a quick bite. Was so much fun. Great atmosphere. Lots of TVs to watch sports. Cant wait to go back.
Had the Oklahoma burger. It was phenomenal.  Side of onion rings ( battered). They were the best I can recall having. Service was exceptional.  All around top notch, my current go to for burgers out.

Dear lord, a competitor to the infamous taco bell crunchwrap supreme. This is the truth. Super flavourful and rich. Toss a bit of Valentina on top and you got a 1-way ticket to flavourtown! Don t make the same mistake I did. I went to DL Chicken thinking it was there, it is ONLY served at DL burgers. BUT! You can also be like me and have both, but prepare yourself! And if you can share with a friend (socially distanced, of course)
Good burgers! Quick service with a happy smile! Various arcade games, photo booth and pool around the perimeter. Conveniently located neat the train station.

Sweet little party bar could see it getting wild in there. The 20 dollar burger fries and beer was an awesome value, the fries were a bit crispy though. Service was good and if I find myself at the bus station for a couple hours Ill be back

Not sure why this wonderful local establishment isn t getting higher rating! I ve been picking up my takeouts here a couple of times during covid and their service and food have been excellent! The Lee s honey dip spicy chicken burger is so good, we are happy to break our paleo diet just to inhale them! And their fries are seasoned well and super crispy, so are their onion rings - large size at only $4 each - I couldn t even get these at that price when I was a kid a couple of decades ago   Highly recommend!
Great spot to watch the game, play some pinball, and have one of the best damn burgers in the city!

this place is always consistent and always good. lettuce is always fresh (seriously such an issue with some burger places around here) and they hit the vegan options nail on the head. burgers are messy, but in my opinion thats what makes them so good Vegetarian options: vegan chicken sandwich, vegan impossible burger, vegan sauce & vegan cheese. vegan side salad available

One of my favourite burger joints in the city. Nice selection of burgers, cooked in the popular smash-burger fashion. My personal favourite is the Americana, a great homage to the big Mac, but elevated to perfection. Sides are all solid. Onion rings are a big standout with their smokey-dilly batter. Good beer list as well, with rotating taps. Venue always has the game on. Whichever one your looking for. Lots of arcade machines well, with a wide range of pinball machines to choose from.

Excellent burgers! Best in the city!  They use quality ingredients and their beef is from Two Rivers which if people know their beef know thats legit.   Their fries are the bomb as well, super crispy.  Cant wait to be back!
Thr Bartender made suprisingly awesome fancy cocktails. Pinball and fancy cocktails, what more could a girl ask for?
Best burger in the world..got the hotest  burger it burned my sole
Awesome classic American diner style smash burgers, and perfectly crispy fries.
This place is good. They love burgers, chicken, and making people happy. Fries are great too. Appreciate the attention to detail and customer service. Highly recommend!
Greasy and delicious burgers!! Lets not lie, they will ruin ruin your diet, but youll be smiling when it does!
Not really a service, but very good!
The Its always Sunny chicken sammy was the best Ive had in a long time!
Tendies are huge! New menu items too now. Stadium nachos are legit. Also they are all super safe with gloves and masks always. Prolly best bar food atm
Superfun and delicious
Food coma burgers and fries. Really good eats and a great place to chill and drink.
Some damn fine crispy chicken sandwich. Almost always a line up, not sure how long it takes when the line is really long, but for many its worth it.
Downlow burgers. The best burgers in town. You must try if you are srz bout burg.
Burgers are excellent. French onion double is the way to go.
Very juicy burgers with very friendly staff.
Best onion rings ever, burger, and chilli fries were solid too.
Super fun atmosphere! Awesome burgers
Literally THEE BEST chicken spot in all of the lower mainland!
Get the onion rings!
If I died choking on food this is where I would peacefully rest
Amazing burgers. Great atmosphere.
Best burgers in town!!
Burgers were amazing!
The Fungi Burger is amaaaaaaaazing!
great taste low prices
These guys are awesome.
Great burger!
Absolutely delicious.
Really good burger!
Awesome burgers and fries

First time here.  The sign outside does not say DownLow. It says The American. Its more bar than anything - the tables are great for large groups.  The food was very good and very messy.  However, the pop was flat. Our server was very excellent.
The food was good, but not worth the price
Great burgers, nice chill atmosphere
While the burgers there are just as common as any good restaurants, the beer-battered onion rings there are special. The flavour is unique so it is a must-try.
Mighty fine pub grub with good specials. I prefer their chicken but the beef burgers are pretty good,  too.

Down Low Burgers, or the American as its also known is a pretty cool. I love pinball, so having a range of machines to blow a few dollars on was great fun. Service was great, beer range good. Lots of people rave about the burgers, but this was a let down for me. I had the Fat Boy. Very messy and whats with the serving it like take out in a bag. Ill be back, but Ill try the fried chicken next time.
Good spot, mushy buns dont take saucy burgers well (or travel well) otherwise yummy and straightforward. Nothing stands out other than its a fun spot to hang with homies and have good pub burgers.
Decent food. Prefer their original location DL chicken on Commercial
Pretty good burger. One of the better ones in town
great atmosphere with good quality staffing. would definitely recommend lunch for a decent price. GREAT BURGERS
My go to everytime I wanna hang out with friends and get tasty food and some beer
Great food with fast friendly service
pretty good. chilli fries are the best.
Taco burger was pretty good
Food and service was great!
Vegetarian options: Multiple tasty vegetarian options. Food
Very nice atmosphere..
Loved the burger! Definitely would come for it, but only if I were in the area. Wings were breaded so wasnt my fave. Dark and Stormy was good but didnt taste like one. Good random cocktail though!
Dont order the chicken burger, its 3 chicken strips in a bun and impossible to hold without falling apart
The burgers are basically cafeteria food, smushed in a wrapper, probably reheated...but it isnt terrible. Just an ok place for a burger, better place to hang out and drink, and eat if youre starving.
Mid burgers, good fries, cool vibes, but got my order wrong...
